SIMPLE: install
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Install
<hw>In*stall"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Installed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Installing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>installer</ets>, LL. <ets>installare</ets>, fr. pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + OHG. <ets>stal</ets> a place, stall, G.
<ets>stall</ets>, akin to E. <ets>stall</ets>: cf. It.
<ets>installare</ets>. See <er>Stall</er>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>instal</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To set in a seat; to give a place to; establish
(one) in a place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She <qex>installed</qex> her guest hospitably by the fireside.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To place in an office, rank, or order; to invest
with any charge by the usual ceremonies; to instate; to induct; <as>as,
to <ex>install</ex> an ordained minister as pastor of a church; to
<ex>install</ex> a college president.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Unworthily⟦br⟧
Thou wast <qex>installed</qex> in that high degree.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Installation</ent>⟦br⟧
